62\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001262\u003C/a> (Taormina). Although dated on the grounds of letter forms to the C2-1 BC by Manni Piraino, the evidence from the necropolis suggests the range C3-2 BC is more plausible.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":257,"html":258},"bibliography","\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Salinas NSA 1886 464 no.b \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Kaibel 1890 \u003Ca href=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\" target=\"_blank\">382d\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Hoffmann 1904 5208d \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000817\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000817\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Manni Piraino 1973 123 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000531\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000531\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Sofia 2015 107 and fig.110 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001575\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001575\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  ",{"id":260,"html":261},"handnote","\u003Cp>Regular plain letters. Phi is slightly taller than the rest, but with a small circular eye; sigma has horizontal top and bottom bars, with the diagonals joined by a curve; omicron is smaller than the other letters and mid-line.\u003C/p> Line 1  30-35  Interlineation line 1 to 2  NA  ",{"id":263,"html":264},"license"," Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence.  ",[266,268,271,272],{"html":267},"Unknown",{"id":269,"lang":129,"html":270},"edition-interpretive","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/